I recently had the opportunity to share on @daytimetvshow how important it is to build a personal brand.

I had a great time working alongside with @dannynewtv, and here are some of the takeaways from my segment:

1️⃣ Start your personal brand today.

It's as easy as pressing a button and hitting record.

All you need to do is tell people who you are and what you do! 

2️⃣ You're gonna get judged.

Let's just deal with that. It's gonna be normal. 

The moment you put yourself out there, it's going to happen. 

Most people don't make it in life not because they can't start, but because they’re worried about what other people will think. 

3️⃣ When you build your personal brand, magic will happen.

Opportunities, contacts, and cash flow will come,

And you'll be able to leverage that and do anything you want. 

If you want to grow your personal brand today and get yourself seen in the media, dm me and let's get you started.

node.text:
Look, a lot of people have got the idea of PR wrong.

They want to put in $1 and get $2 back.

Here’s the thing: if you want a direct ROI with your money, you’re better off using ads.

PR gives you so much MORE than just some money back.

PR gives you instant credibility, trust, authority, exposure, amplification, etc.

This leads to SO much more down the road.

You can walk into any room and not have to justify yourself. You don’t have to prove yourself because people will already KNOW who you are.

So the ROI on PR is instant.

That’s something that ads can’t get you.

node.text:
One thing that's important to me is kids. I love children. 😃

I also love that we are able to help kids and train them to be confident and believe in themselves from such an early age. 💯 

Think about how different the whole world would be if we trained kids to truly believe in themselves. 🌎 

In today's video, I talked with the soon-to-be-famous Claire as she tells us a little bit about herself and what she wants to do. 🙌🏽

Do you think we should be investing into the future of today’s kids? Share your thoughts in the comments below 👇🏽

So, I was in Miami and I was craving a bit of sugar. 🍭 

I noticed two restaurants side by side; one sold ice cream, the other sold pie.

I chose to eat at the pie place. 🥧 

Now, why did I choose pie?

Was it because the pies are better? No.

Was it because I was craving pies? No.

It was because of the influence that the pie shop had. 🏆 

You see, there was a crowd. There were lines. People looked EXCITED to be there. 😃

But the ice cream shop looked empty, nobody looked happy to be there. 🙁

This example ties in perfectly with your brand and influence. 🌟 

If you don’t have the influence, 🏅 

If you don’t have the people on your page, 📱 

If people aren’t talking about your brand, 🗣

They will choose someone else over you. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 

No matter what industry or niche you’re in,

Take a look at how your influence is today.

If you’re wanting to amplify your message in the media and get the attention you deserve, 📰 

Dm me ‘MEDIA’ and we’ll get you started! 📲

node.title: WHY DID I CHOOSE PIES OVER ICE CREAM? 👇🏽

node.text:

•
I used to get so caught up on all the things like:
 
⏰ When to post
🤔 How to post
#️⃣ Hashtags
📝 The perfect content
🤪 The emojis next to the words
 
But guess what?
 
It doesn’t matter. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 
 
You’ll get caught up with that and forget about the bigger picture.
 
What is the why? What are you trying to do?
 
Focus on the message. 📲 
 
Focus on attracting the people that you want to work with. 👋🏽 
 
You will not lose out on people because the emoji next the caption is wrong. 👎🏽 
 
You’re going to lose out because you’re gonna be spending time on the wrong thing. 🙅🏽‍♂️
 
So it doesn’t matter who you are, what you do, what you’re trying to do,
 
Get out of your head and start putting out your message in unique ways.
 
Because most people are sitting in their head way too much and are losing because of that.

node.title: Are You Sitting in Your Head?

node.text:
One of the questions I get all the time is: how do I start to grow my personal brand?

Here is the easiest step to start with, no matter what platform you’re using:

You need to start posting content. 📸 

Start with doing THREE pieces of content per week.

And before you go crazy wondering how you’ll manage that, relax. 

Here’s the plan.

1️⃣ EDUCATIONAL 
First piece of content needs to be an educational post about your industry.

You’re the expert in your niche, so post some tips for other people!

2️⃣ RESULTS 
Second piece of content is results.

People love it when they see other’s saying great things about you.

So share a screenshot, a text message, a video testimonial, etc.

3️⃣ PERSONAL 
the third piece of content needs to be something personal.

Don’t just put up a nice picture with your wife, your girlfriend, or you eating a slice of pizza.

But add a story behind it. People want to get to know YOU.

So once again, start posting three times a week and watch your brand grow! 🚀

If you have any questions, feel free to connect and send me a message OR book a call with the link in the bio 📲

I’m here to help you grow in 2021!

Jay

📲 https://aosagency.co/call

node.title: 🤓 How Do I Grow My Personal Brand 🤓

node.text:
.
.
It’s really exciting that we all get to decide what we wanna do and who we want to be. 😃

It’s the start of the new year and it’s your chance not just to listen to your head, but to listen to your heart and your gut. ❤️ 

So, as your friend I give you permission to try everything out. 👋🏽

Because even I am still trying to figure it out! 😅

And the great thing about this whole world at the moment is that you can be anyone you want to be. 😎

 You can try anything you want to try. 🥸

The only person stopping you is you. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 

So what is it that you want to do this year? Let me know in the comments below. 👇🏽

node.text:
You need to put in the hours if you want to win. 🕙

So many people want the life they see online, the Ferrari’s and the fancy stuff, 🥂 

But half of it is fake anyways. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 

If you want to live the life you really want to live, 🏅 

You have to skill up, sacrifice, and put in the hours 🌙 

Because that’s what you got to do if you want to play on a higher level. 🏆

I recently had the opportunity to share on @daytimetvshow how important it is to build a personal brand.

I had a great time working alongside with @dannynewtv, and here are some of the takeaways from my segment:

1️⃣ Start your personal brand today.

It's as easy as pressing a button and hitting record.

All you need to do is tell people who you are and what you do! 

2️⃣ You're gonna get judged.

Let's just deal with that. It's gonna be normal. 

The moment you put yourself out there, it's going to happen. 

Most people don't make it in life not because they can't start, but because they’re worried about what other people will think. 

3️⃣ When you build your personal brand, magic will happen.

Opportunities, contacts, and cash flow will come,

And you'll be able to leverage that and do anything you want. 

If you want to grow your personal brand today and get yourself seen in the media, dm me and let's get you started.

node.text:
Look, a lot of people have got the idea of PR wrong.

They want to put in $1 and get $2 back.

Here’s the thing: if you want a direct ROI with your money, you’re better off using ads.

PR gives you so much MORE than just some money back.

PR gives you instant credibility, trust, authority, exposure, amplification, etc.

This leads to SO much more down the road.

You can walk into any room and not have to justify yourself. You don’t have to prove yourself because people will already KNOW who you are.

So the ROI on PR is instant.

That’s something that ads can’t get you.

So, I was in Miami and I was craving a bit of sugar. 🍭 

I noticed two restaurants side by side; one sold ice cream, the other sold pie.

I chose to eat at the pie place. 🥧 

Now, why did I choose pie?

Was it because the pies are better? No.

Was it because I was craving pies? No.

It was because of the influence that the pie shop had. 🏆 

You see, there was a crowd. There were lines. People looked EXCITED to be there. 😃

But the ice cream shop looked empty, nobody looked happy to be there. 🙁

This example ties in perfectly with your brand and influence. 🌟 

If you don’t have the influence, 🏅 

If you don’t have the people on your page, 📱 

If people aren’t talking about your brand, 🗣

They will choose someone else over you. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 

No matter what industry or niche you’re in,

Take a look at how your influence is today.

If you’re wanting to amplify your message in the media and get the attention you deserve, 📰 

Dm me ‘MEDIA’ and we’ll get you started! 📲

node.text:
I WAS INTIMIDATED BY YOU…

And that’s what the guy said to me at the success conference last week.

He said to me, “Jay, I’ve been watching you for a while, but I have to be honest with you. When I first saw you online, I was a little bit intimidated by you.” 👀 

So I asked him, “Why was that?” 🧐 

And he said, “Because you look so put together, professional, and pretty much perfect. But once I actually got to know you, I realized that you’re a really down-to-earth guy that likes to have a lot of fun. My perception of you changed.” 😃 

When I heard that, I gave him a fist-bump and thanked him for being honest. 👊🏽

But hearing that got me thinking, and I wanted to share with you today that hey, I’m just a normal guy. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 

I know my posts and content can sometimes come across as if I’ve got it all together, but I don’t.

😓 I struggle.
😞 I get lonely.
🙅🏽‍♂️ I get rejected.
👎🏽 I get in trouble.
💔 I get my heart broken.
💋 I get cheated on.
🤥 People lie to me.
🛋 I know what it’s like to have no money and sleep on couches.
☀️ Sometimes all I’m trying to do is get through the day.
👋🏽 I’m just a normal person like you.

But I want to share this because I know how important it is to reveal what I’m sharing with you now.

I’m trying to figure out me, and I think that’s why I ran around the world for so long actually. ✈️ 

Not just because I love to travel, but because I was trying to figure out who I was. And it’s still something I’m doing.

So if you’re still reading this, I just was to remind you once again that I’m just a guy from Australia who has a dream and wants to do more, be more, and help others become more. 💯 

And if I can help you along your journey, let me help you. 🙌🏽

And if you’ve ever watched me or listened to me or been inspired by me, thank you. 

Because you’re giving me the chance to share how I feel and who I am. ❤️ 

Thank you for that. 🙏🏽

‼️WHY WOULD I BELIEVE YOU⁉️
ft. @therealbradlea 

If you were going to the gym and you wanted to get a 6 pack,

Are you going to take advice from someone that’s 600 pounds? 🤔 

Probably not. 👎🏽

If you were going to become a millionaire, would you take advice from someone that’s only made $1,000? 💰 

Probably not. 👎🏽

It’s the same thing with your social media. 📲 

🚀 If you’re trying to build your personal brand,

👀 If you’re trying to get attention,

💪🏽 If you’re trying to get authority, 

✔️ If you’re trying to get verified,

Wouldn’t you take advice from someone who has it already, 

Who is already doing it right now?

Absolutely. 👍🏽

And this is really important. 🚨 

When you work with people, look at what they’ve done. 📝 

Have they done it? 
Are they doing it now? 
Can they relate to you? 
Do you like them?

That’s really important when you’re looking for help and looking for a coach. 

Try to work with people who have had the success and that are doing it now. 🏆 

Because not only have they had the success, 

They’ll be able to take you to the finish line. 🏁 

If you want me to take you to the finish line, dm me ‘GROW’ and I’ll take you there today. 💯

I used to get so caught up on all the things like:
 
⏰ When to post
🤔 How to post
#️⃣ Hashtags
📝 The perfect content
🤪 The emojis next to the words
 
But guess what?
 
It doesn’t matter. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 
 
You’ll get caught up with that and forget about the bigger picture.
 
What is the why? What are you trying to do?
 
Focus on the message. 📲 
 
Focus on attracting the people that you want to work with. 👋🏽 
 
You will not lose out on people because the emoji next the caption is wrong. 👎🏽 
 
You’re going to lose out because you’re gonna be spending time on the wrong thing. 🙅🏽‍♂️
 
So it doesn’t matter who you are, what you do, what you’re trying to do,
 
Get out of your head and start putting out your message in unique ways.
 
Because most people are sitting in their head way too much and are losing because of that.

node.text:
What Does 10x Mean to You? 👇🏽

So last week I attended the @10xgrowthconference in Miami, brought to you by the main man himself, @grantcardone. 💯

Let me just tell you, wow wow wow. 🤯 

Think of a music concert mixed with a business conference, with lights, energy, and winners all put together in one room. 🌟 

It was the best conference I’ve ever been to.

The speakers Grant brought, the messages that I heard, the people that I met, I’m blown away. 💥 

Every speaker Grant brought on stage, he always asked one question: what does 10x mean to you? 🧐 

Now, I’m not sure what 10x means to you, but what it means to me is 10xing everything about your life. 💪🏽

Because I believe you can do more, you can be more, and you can become more.

So the question you have to ask yourself today is, how are you 10xing your life today? 🏆 

What do you want to do?

Where do you want to go?

Who do you want to be?

I’m giving you permission today to do more. 🙌🏽

And the only reason you’re not, is yourself. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 

But one thing I can say to you is, you need to be around other winners in your life. 👥

Look at the people around you.

Ask yourself, are these people winners, or are these people losers? 👀 

So one of the ways you can 10x your life is find other winners around your life, and that’s exactly why I attend these conferences. ✈️ 

That’s why I hang out with Grant Cardone’s people. 🫂 

Because I know everybody in that room and everybody on stage wants to 10x their life.

So once again, the question you have to ask yourself is, how are you 10xing your life today so you can live the life you want?

Comment below what it is that you’re doing. I want to hear from my WINNERS! 😃

node.text:
One of the questions I get all the time is: how do I start to grow my personal brand?

Here is the easiest step to start with, no matter what platform you’re using:

You need to start posting content. 📸 

Start with doing THREE pieces of content per week.

And before you go crazy wondering how you’ll manage that, relax. 

Here’s the plan.

1️⃣ EDUCATIONAL 
First piece of content needs to be an educational post about your industry.

You’re the expert in your niche, so post some tips for other people!

2️⃣ RESULTS 
Second piece of content is results.

People love it when they see other’s saying great things about you.

So share a screenshot, a text message, a video testimonial, etc.

3️⃣ PERSONAL 
the third piece of content needs to be something personal.

Don’t just put up a nice picture with your wife, your girlfriend, or you eating a slice of pizza.

But add a story behind it. People want to get to know YOU.

So once again, start posting three times a week and watch your brand grow! 🚀

If you have any questions, feel free to connect and send me a message OR book a call with the link in the bio 📲

I’m here to help you grow in 2021!

Jay

📲 https://aosagency.co/call

node.text:
I have something to tell you…

I’ve been fortunate to stand on some of the biggest stages in the world and work for some of the biggest companies in the world. 🌎 

You name it, I’ve worked for them.

McDonalds, Coca Cola, Virgin, Audi…

I’ve spoken in multiple countries, for multiple different people. 🗣

But for a long time throughout my speaking career, I struggled with this thing called the ‘imposter syndrome’, 🎭

The Imposter Syndrome is something where you feel like you’re not at the level that you should be, or you like you’re not qualified to really share and speak. 

And the thing that I realized is that a lot of the time, most of the time, or actually ALL the time, Imposter Syndrome is just what you’re telling yourself. It’s the stories in your head. 💭 

You don’t just get invited to work with billion dollar companies and speak in front of thousands of people if you’re no one. 🤷🏽‍♂️ 

There’s a REASON why they booked you. There’s a reason why they want you.

And it isn’t because you have a cool hairstyle and you’re from Australia. 😁

So it doesn’t matter what you’re trying to do,
Or where you’re trying to go,
Or what kind of content you’re trying to produce,
Or how you’re trying to tell your message to the world,

You will deal with imposter syndrome. You will feel like you’re not at the level that you should be at.

Now, I’m not saying that you shouldn’t be practicing and skilling up; everyone should be improving. 💯 

But most of the time what blocks us is when we tell ourselves that we’re not good enough.

Let me tell you something today my friends:

You ARE good enough. You ARE great. 😊

So go out and tell the world who you are, what you do, and what your story is.
